    <string name="congratulations_on_maintaining_a_balanced_stress_level">Congratulations on maintaining a balanced stress level!</string>
    <string name="tips_to_stay_balanced">Tips to Stay Balanced:</string>
    <string name="tip_1_title">1. Routine Maintenance:</string>
    <string name="tip_1_desc">Stick to routines that promote a balanced lifestyle, including regular exercise, a healthy diet, and sufficient sleep.</string>
    <string name="tip_2_title">2. Mindfulness Practices:</string>
    <string name="tip_2_desc">Engage in mindfulness exercises such as yoga or meditation to enhance your resilience against stress.</string>
    <string name="tip_3_title">3. Monitor Stressors:</string>
    <string name="tip_3_desc">Keep an eye on common stress triggers and address them proactively to prevent them from disrupting your balance.</string>
    <string name="faqs">FAQs</string>
    <string name="faq_q1_hrv">Why is the balanced zone ideal?</string>
    <string name="faq_a1_hrv">The balanced zone indicates that your autonomic nervous system is in a state of equilibrium, meaning you are neither over-stressed nor under-recovered.</string>
    <string name="faq_q2_hrv">When should I check my HRV?</string>
    <string name="faq_a2_hrv">It\'s best to check your HRV at consistent times, such as every morning upon waking or before/after specific activities, to track trends over time.</string>
    <string name="faq_q3_hrv">What should I do if my HRV is in the Stressed zone?</string>
    <string name="faq_a3_hrv">If you are in the stressed zone, consider recovery activities like deep breathing, light movement, or ensuring you get extra rest.</string>
